Lagos- Nigerians have been alerted of fake COVID-19 result certificates being sold in Lagos state. The alarm has been raised by the Lagos state government on the issue of COVID-19 results. The Government of Lagos state through Prof. Akin Abayomi, the Commissioner for Health, on Monday raised the alarm over fake COVID-19 certificates on sale in the state. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Abayomi spoke at a press conference while giving update on second wave of the virus in Lagos. He said it has come to the attention of the government that a number of people who came into the country were patronising individuals who sell fake COVID-19 results certificates. Second Wave Of COVID-19: Abia NOA Tasks Citizens To Celebrate Responsibly COVID-19 Second Wave: 22 Of 42 Patients In UATH Surviving Through Oxygenation Abayomi said government was on top of the issue and is currently putting machinery in place to apprehend those doing such unscrupulous businesses. The commissioner also warned that there had been an increase in positive cases from inbound travellers, which rose to eight percent this week. He said: “Positivity for inbound travelers is on the rise (eight this week, four percent cumulative) as Nigerians in Diaspora return to spend Christmas in Lagos.” “It has come to our attention that a number of people are patronizing individuals that sell fake COVID-19 results.” “We are currently putting in processes to identify both buyers and sellers and we will not hesitate to prosecute either to the full extent of the law.” Abayomi further explained that the reason for the second wave of COVID-19 was due to reopening of schools, General Laxity, False Sense, of Security and Non-adherence to guidelines; opening of the economy, variant, large religious congregation and social gathering and entertainment. He revealed that Lagos State h